# direnv config — OPTIONAL, for Mac/Linux developers.
#
# What this does:
#   When you `cd` into this repo, direnv auto-loads .env into your shell so
#   `claude` and `opencode` can read ${TAVILY_API_KEY}, ${JIRA_*}, etc.
#   without going through the `bun claude` wrapper.
#
# Setup (one-time per developer):
#   1. Install direnv:
#        macOS:   brew install direnv
#        Linux:   apt install direnv  (or your distro's package manager)
#   2. Add the shell hook to your ~/.zshrc or ~/.bashrc:
#        eval "$(direnv hook zsh)"     # for zsh
#        eval "$(direnv hook bash)"    # for bash
#   3. Reload your shell, cd into this repo, then run: direnv allow
#      (Required for security — direnv won't load any .envrc without explicit approval.)
#
# Windows note:
#   direnv has friction on Windows (requires WSL or Git Bash, and PowerShell
#   profile access). Windows users: stick with `bun claude` / `bun opencode`
#   from package.json — same .env, cross-platform, no extra setup.
#
# Per-developer overrides:
#   Put extra exports in .envrc.local (gitignored). This file sources it last.

# Portable POSIX loader — works on direnv 2.21+ (does NOT require 2.30's
# dotenv_if_exists, so older Linux distros / corporate installs still work).
if [ -f .env ]; then
  set -a
  . .env
  set +a
fi
if [ -f .envrc.local ]; then
  . .envrc.local
fi
